2 unit(s) Baguette
2 unit(s) Tomato
125 grams Mozzarella
1 sachet(s) Green Pesto
40 grams Salad Leaves
1 sachet(s) Balsamic Glaze
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Butter (Optional)
to taste Oil

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Thinly slice the tomato.
Drain and thinly slice the mozzarella.
Halve the baguettes lengthways. Butter the bread if you like.
Pop the baguettes —cut-side up—into the oven to warm through, 2-3 mins.
TIP: To avoid turning on your oven, you can warm the baguette in the toaster instead.

Spread the pesto onto the cut side of the base of each baguette.
Top with the salad leaves (as much or as little as you like).
Lay the tomato, then the mozzarella on top of the salad.
Drizzle some oil and the balsamic glaze over the top.
Season with salt and pepper. Sandwich closed with the top half of the baguette.

To serve, slice each baguette in half widthways.
Divide between plates.
Serve any remaining salad on the side.